   "source": [
    "## 1. NumPy Convolution Implementation\n",
    "\n",
    "Recall the formula for a discrete 2D cross-correlation (convolution):\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Output}(i, j) = \\sum_{m=0}^{K_h-1} \\sum_{n=0}^{K_w-1} I(i + m, j + n) K(m, n)$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "def convolve2d_basic(image, kernel):\n",
    "    ih, iw = image.shape\n",
    "    kh, kw = kernel.shape\n",
    "    out_h = ih - kh + 1\n",
    "    out_w = iw - kw + 1\n",
    "    \n",
    "    output = np.zeros((out_h, out_w))\n",
    "    for i in range(out_h):\n",
    "        for j in range(out_w):\n",
    "            output[i, j] = np.sum(image[i:i+kh, j:j+kw] * kernel)\n",
    "    return output\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test image and vertical Sobel kernel\n",
    "img = np.array([\n",
    "    [0, 0, 255, 255],\n",
    "    [0, 0, 255, 255],\n",
    "    [0, 0, 255, 255],\n",
    "    [0, 0, 255, 255]\n",
    "])\n",
    "kernel = np.array([\n",
    "    [-1, 0, 1],\n",
    "    [-2, 0, 2],\n",
    "    [-1, 0, 1]\n",
    "])\n",
    "print(\"Convolution Output:\\n\", convolve2d_basic(img, kernel))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Exercises & Solutions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Exercise 1:\n",
    "Calculate the output size for an input image of shape $224 \\times 224$ passing through a Conv layer with kernel size $7 \\times 7$, stride $2$, and padding $3$.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Solution:\n",
    "$$\\text{Output Size} = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{W - K + 2P}{S} \\right\\rfloor + 1 = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{224 - 7 + 2(3)}{2} \\right\\rfloor + 1 = \\left\\lfloor \\frac{223}{2} \\right\\rfloor + 1 = 111 + 1 = 112$$"
  }
 ],
